# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for high-value paths.
#
# Combined with branch protection ("Require review from Code Owners"),
# this means PRs touching anything under these paths cannot merge until
# the listed owner(s) approve the change. See:
#   https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# When the team grows, replace `@ingemar-enclaves` with a security team
# (e.g. `@enclaves-finance/security`) so the rule scales without
# touching this file per-person.

# Default owner for anything not matched below.
*                                @ingemar-enclaves

# On-chain code — the actual bytecode that gets deployed.
/contracts/                      @ingemar-enclaves

# Deploy / verify scripts and the deploy-topology JSON examples that
# downstream tooling reads.
/scripts/                        @ingemar-enclaves
/deployments/                    @ingemar-enclaves

# CI, build, and supply-chain configuration. A change here can quietly
# weaken every other guard rail, so it gets the same scrutiny as
# contracts.
/.github/                        @ingemar-enclaves
/hardhat.config.ts               @ingemar-enclaves
/package.json                    @ingemar-enclaves
/package-lock.json               @ingemar-enclaves
/tsconfig.json                   @ingemar-enclaves
/tsconfig.build.json             @ingemar-enclaves
/.solhint.json                   @ingemar-enclaves
/.gitattributes                  @ingemar-enclaves

# Security policy itself.
/SECURITY.md                     @ingemar-enclaves
